{"id": "EUVD-2023-59704", "enisaUuid": "690cf75d-6269-3472-b1e0-6378921145ab", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nBluetooth: Fix possible deadlock in rfcomm_sk_state_change\n\nsyzbot reports a possible deadlock in rfcomm_sk_state_change [1].\nWhile rfcomm_sock_connect acquires the sk lock and waits for\nthe rfcomm lock, rfcomm_sock_release could have the rfcomm\nlock and hit a deadlock for acquiring the sk lock.\nHere's a simplified flow:\n\nrfcomm_sock_connect:\n  lock_sock(sk)\n  rfcomm_dlc_open:\n    rfcomm_lock()\n\nrfcomm_sock_release:\n  rfcomm_sock_shutdown:\n    rfcomm_lock()\n    __rfcomm_dlc_close:\n        rfcomm_k_state_change:\n\t  lock_sock(sk)\n\nThis patch drops the sk lock before calling rfcomm_dlc_open to\navoid the possible deadlock and holds sk's reference count to\nprevent use-after-free after rfcomm_dlc_open completes.", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T16:43:44", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T17:20:23", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/98aec50ff7f60cc6f2d6a4396b475c547e58b04d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/17511bd84871f4a6106cb335616e086880313f3f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1d80d57ffcb55488f0ec0b77928d4f82d16b6a90", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53016"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53016"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "092da12c-8aac-3072-94f2-daa7468c6b51", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "3153a448-5dc3-393f-abda-e72bc3a59b23", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.91"}, {"id": "3d7721e6-4fae-3a74-9dca-c55158e55913", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.15"}, {"id": "98bc152c-f492-3f9c-b7c5-28ac5ebb713b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "a1a2f710-0c7a-3208-b6cc-cd32968e6f5d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1804fdf6e494e5e2938c65d8391690b59bcff897 <1d80d57ffcb55488f0ec0b77928d4f82d16b6a90"}, {"id": "c11fbd2b-f56d-30b7-a93b-169ac60c1a04", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1804fdf6e494e5e2938c65d8391690b59bcff897 <98aec50ff7f60cc6f2d6a4396b475c547e58b04d"}, {"id": "ce823107-2e63-3bf9-b42f-04998e3b3441", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.9"}, {"id": "fbf07c8a-6a5d-350b-a87d-d9926497570a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1804fdf6e494e5e2938c65d8391690b59bcff897 <17511bd84871f4a6106cb335616e086880313f3f"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "36bac780-dd63-3eeb-b331-7c27d123a976", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}